article.headline: Boston scores its most points in three years

images.name: Pierce_Paul 020306 inline
images.caption: Paul Pierce led Boston nine players in double figures with his 22 points.

article.linkText: Celtics put nine in double figures in ripping Magic
article.story:
BOSTON (AP) -- Not since Larry Bird was around have the Boston Celtics had a season like this. Nine Celtics scored in double figures for the first time since Bird's final season a decade ago, and Boston had its highest point total in three years Wednesday night to beat the Orlando Magic 130-110. "I don't see why we can't put up 100 points a game, with the talent we've got on this ballclub," said Paul Pierce, who had 22 points. "Everybody contributed." Antoine Walker had 16 points, 14 rebounds and seven assists as the Celtics topped their best this year by 20 points, scoring their most points since a triple-overtime game in 1999 and more than they've had in any regulation game in six years. At 33-27, they have their best record through 60 games since 1991-92, Bird's farewell. Boston also took a 2½-game lead over Orlando in the Eastern Conference playoff race and clinched the edge in a potential tiebreaker with a 3-1 head-to-head record. "We're fighting for homecourt advantage, and when we look up in the East, we're right behind the second and third spots," Pierce said. "We might be seeing Orlando in the first round. This is a huge win." A night after Orlando coach Doc Rivers was ejected for arguing with the officials, the team lost its fourth consecutive game to wrap up the longest road trip in franchise history. In seven games over 11 nights, they went 2-5. Tracy McGrady scored 17 points in only 20 minutes, and Darrell Armstrong, Pat Garrity and Monty Williams had 16 apiece for Orlando, which scratched center Horace Grant from the starting lineup because of back spasms. "They did the best they could, being tired, being short-handed, being the seventh game," Rivers said. "We had all the excuses. I was actually hoping we wouldn't use them, but we did. That was a throwaway game." Boston took a 10-2 lead to start the game, but Orlando trailed by as few as seven, 64-57, after Garrity hit a long 3-pointer to start the third quarter. Tony Delk and McGrady traded 3-pointers before Pierce hit one from 26 feet to spark a 9-0 Celtics run. Vitaly Potapenko stole the ball to help set up Kenny Anderson's 3, then Potapenko blocked Andrew DeClercq's shot and made a layup at the other end to make it 76-60. Twice this season the Celtics have scored 110. They reached that mark with 9:33 left to play; soon after, coach Jim O'Brien started clearing his bench, and garbage time was on. Boston has won consecutive games after losing four in a row. Eric Williams and Kedrick Brown each had two points in six minutes, and Tony Battie did not dress because of swelling in his right leg. On March 4, 1992, Bird had 17 points and 14 rebounds; Dee Brown had 14 points and 11 assists; Joe Kleine had 15 points and 10 rebounds and Kevin Gamble scored 18 to lead nine Celtics in double figures. Kevin McHale did not play that game because of a sprained ankle and John Bagley also did not play. Game notes
Despite his association with hated New York, Patrick Ewing got a nice ovation when he entered the game in the first quarter. He finished with zero points on 0-for-3 shooting in nine minutes. ... Rivers was fined $7,500 by the NBA for failing to quickly leave the court following an ejection and criticizing game officials on Tuesday. ... Early in the fourth quarter, Walter McCarty hurdled the press table and wound up three rows back in the stands while chasing a loose ball. He went back the way he came. ... The biggest hand of the night was for New England Patriots Troy Brown and Jermaine Wiggins in the crowd.
